define i1 @add_nuw_decomp_recursive() {
  %add = add nuw nsw i64 -9223372036854775808, 10
  %cmp = icmp uge i64 %add, 10
  ret i1 %cmp
}

define i1 @sub_nuw_i64_signed_min_const(i64 %a) {
entry:
  %neg2 = sub nuw i64 0, -9223372036854775808
  %c = icmp ugt i64 %neg2, 0
  ret i1 %c
}

comments.body:
 

> Looks like the compile-time cost of doing this is very high: [dtcxzyw/llvm-opt-benchmark#3454 (comment)](https://github.com/dtcxzyw/llvm-opt-benchmark/pull/3454#issuecomment-3881987708) (I expect this is due to the added constraints, not due to computeConstantRange.)

I have recovered the compile time hit to a large extent by restricting this to operands and operands of operands of (non eq/ne) icmp instructions. 

@dtcxzyw Could you please trigger another compile time and IR impact test? Thanks!
